      "FacilityID": 1000002679,
      "SummaryText": "al release during the past five years which meets the criteria for an accidental release per 40 CFR 68.42.  An incident on 10/11/08 as outlined in Section 6 resulted in the release of 3300 pounds of sulfuric acid mist, equivalent to 2826 pounds of Oleum.  The information which is included regarding the release which occurred on October 11, 2008 is based upon INDSPEC's Investigation to date and includes information on claims which have been submitted to INDSPEC.  In regard to such claims, INDSPEC has not currently undergone a complete investigation to determine the claims validity.\n\nEmergency Response Program (A\u00c2\u00a7 68.155(f))\n\nThe Petrolia, PA facility has established a written emergency response plan and maintains an emergency response team (A\u00c2\u00bfERTA\u00c2\u00bf) trained in these emergency response procedures.  All plant personnel are trained in evacuation procedures and in-plant drills are conducted periodically.  The drills are used to test the response time of the Emergency Response Team, to test the plant employee accountability program, and to activate the plant's Emergency Command Center (A\u00c2\u00bfECCA\u00c2\u00bf).  In addition, the Petrolia, PA facility has developed a Special Situations Plan (A\u00c2\u00bfSSPA\u00c2\u00bf) which is a program designed for responding to emergencies that may have impacts beyond the immediate plant and is a supplement to the Emergency Response Plan.  The Special Situation Plan links the local response to the Corporate Emergency Response Center located in Dallas, Texas.\n\nThe facility supports the efforts of the Butler County Local Emergency Planning Committee (A\u00c2\u00bfLEPCA\u00c2\u00bf), which includes industrial and public entities.\n\nPlanned Changes to Improve Safety (A\u00c2\u00a7 68.155(g))\n\nThe Petrolia, PA facility constantly tries to improve the safety of the processes through annual reviews of our plant procedures, near misses and incident investigation programs, and a program soliciting safety and environmental suggestions from the plant employees.\n\nCertification Statement\n\nTo the best of the"
